# Privacy Policy for Unit Converter

**Effective Date:** April 19, 2025

## Introduction

Thank you for choosing to use our Unit Converter application ("App"). This Privacy Policy is designed to help you understand what information we collect, why we collect it, and how we handle your data.

## Information We Don't Collect

Our Unit Converter App is designed with your privacy in mind. We want to be clear that:

- We do not collect any personal information from you
- We do not require you to create an account
- We do not track your location
- We do not store your conversion history
- We do not access your contacts, photos, files, or other device content
- We do not use cookies or similar tracking technologies

## Technical Information Automatically Collected

The only information we may receive is automatically collected by the Google Play Store for basic analytics and crash reporting purposes. This includes:

- App installation and uninstallation statistics
- App crash reports
- Basic device information (device model, Android version)
- Country of download

This information is provided to us in an anonymized, aggregated format and cannot be used to identify individual users. It helps us improve the app's stability and functionality.

## Third-Party Services

### Google Play Services

Our app uses Google Play Services, which may collect information used to identify your device for the purpose of improving the Google Play ecosystem. Please refer to [Google's Privacy Policy](https://policies.google.com/privacy) for more information on how Google uses this data.

### Analytics

We may use Firebase Analytics to collect anonymous usage statistics that help us understand how users interact with our app. This information is used solely to improve our app's functionality and user experience. All analytics data is anonymized and cannot be used to identify individual users.

## Children's Privacy

Our Unit Converter App does not collect personal information from anyone, including children under the age of 13. The app is suitable for users of all ages, and we do not knowingly collect or solicit data from children.

## Your Choices

Since we don't collect personal data, there is no need for specific user controls regarding personal data. However, you can:

- Disable crash reporting through your device settings
- Uninstall the app at any time to remove it from your device completely

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Effective Date" at the top.

You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.

## Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our practices regarding your personal information, please contact us at:

- Email: [your-contact-email@example.com]
- Website: [your-website.com]

## Compliance with Laws

We are committed to complying with all applicable laws, including:

- General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
- California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
- Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA)

Since our app does not collect personal information, many of the data protection regulations' specific requirements regarding data processing, data subject rights, and data transfers do not directly apply. However, we remain committed to the principles of data protection and privacy by design.

## Your Rights

Although we don't collect personal data, you always have the right to:

- Be informed about how your data would be used (if we were to collect it)
- Delete the app from your device at any time
- Contact your local data protection authority if you have concerns about our practices

Thank you for trusting our Unit Converter App. We are committed to maintaining your privacy while providing a useful and efficient unit conversion tool.
